Problem:
class WeatherSimulator {
    private static final int CLEAR = 0, CLOUDY = 1, RAINY = 2;
    private int weather;

    public WeatherSimulator() {
        this.weather = CLEAR;
    }

    public void updateWeather(int humidity, boolean hasLowPressure) {
        if (humidity > 70) {
            if (hasLowPressure) {
                this.weather = RAINY;
            } else {
                this.weather = CLOUDY;
            }
        } else {
            this.weather = CLEAR;
        }
    }

    public int getWeather() {
        return this.weather;
    }
}",

If the `humidity` increases to 75 and `hasLowPressure` remains false, will the weather still be CLEAR?
